annotationA: Unpaired 1 (Upd1) is a secreted glycol-protein that is able to act at a distance as the primary ligand of the JAK/STAT signaling pathway. Although semi-redundant with upd2 and upd3, Upd1 depletion results in embryonic lethality with an atypical gap gene-like segmentation phenotype
annotationB: Unpaired 3 (Upd3) is a "cytokine" (secreted protein) of the Unpaired family that can bind and activate the JAK-STAT receptor dome. Upd3 is induced in hemocytes or in the intestine upon damage to regulate the repair response in these tissues through JAK-STAT activation
